{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"6df1bac1-940f-4fe1-9508-7d3da53b2e4a","content":"Here's how to migrate from `VSTest@3` to Microsoft.Testing.Platform while keeping TRX reports and code coverage:\n\n**1. Update your test project:**\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMSTestRunner>true</EnableMSTestRunner>\n  <OutputType>Exe</OutputType>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\n**2. Replace `VSTest@3` in your pipeline with `dotnet test`:**\n\n```yaml\n- task: DotNetCoreCLI@2\n  displayName: 'Run Tests'\n  inputs:\n    command: 'test'\n    projects: '**/*Tests.csproj'\n    arguments: >\n      --logger \"trx;LogFileName=results.trx\"\n      --results-directory $(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults\n      --collect \"Code Coverage\"\n```\n\n**3. Publish results:**\n\n```yaml\n- task: PublishTestResults@2\n  inputs:\n    testResultsFormat: 'VSTest'\n    testResultsFiles: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.trx'\n\n- task: PublishCodeCoverageResults@2\n  inputs:\n    summaryFileLocation: '$(Agent.TempDirectory)/TestResults/**/*.cobertura.xml'\n```\n\n**Key differences:**\n- Tests are now self-contained executables (no `vstest.console` needed)\n- TRX logger still works via `--logger trx`\n- Code coverage uses `--collect \"Code Coverage\"` (or add the `coverlet.collector` NuGet for Cobertura format)\n\nIf you need Cobertura output specifically, add `coverlet.collector` and use:\n```\n--collect:\"XPlat Code Coverage\"\n```","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"419ab3b7-f23a-4c09-a4c4-f5d8455922e4","outputTokens":413,"requestId":"E3F7:1A0B9E:161D073:18BA3AE:6A052004"},"id":"25a74bbf-cb10-4c38-8349-3b45729effd5","timestamp":"2026-05-14T01:06:21.106Z","parentId":"3263e4d6-c057-4b90-9da7-c761290326bf"}
